Purpose
- Phase 1: fit hyperparameters for AM pipelines against human annotations using a composite loss.

Key components
- evals/
  - Evaluator: loads base+adapters or merged model; builds prompts; optional RAG/COT; parses JSON; computes metrics.
  - Metrics (legacy and modular): fuzzy span F1, relation macroâ€‘F1, count RMSE, graph edit distance, combined score.
  - Datasets: adapter interface for (id, text, gold_struct) iteration.
  - Prompts: minimal default builder for ACC/ARI/ARC/ARIC JSON.
  - Cost: WeightedCost reading weights from config.
- prompts/
  - meta_llama_3.1_8B/
  - 
- generate_llm_prompts.py: Uses the prompt templates to generate prompt files for LLM usage
- hpo.py: placeholder for Optuna/Bayesian search loop (not implemented). 

Config usage
- snowball.phase_1.eval.fuzzy_thr: fuzzy matching threshold.
- snowball.phase_1.eval.loss.w: weight vector [span, relation, count, ged].
- snowball.phase_1.hparams.end2end.*: decoding, rag, cot defaults (if wired by caller).

Status / TODO
- Dataset loaders and HPO loop wiring are not yet implemented.
- For generate_llm_prompts.py, implement prompt generation for CoT, RAG, and CoT + RAG.

